name: NoClassDefFoundError
comment:
Thrown if the Java Virtual Machine or a ClassLoader instance tries to load in the definition of a class (as part of a normal method call or as part of creating a new instance using the new expression) and no definition of the class could be found.

The searched-for class definition existed when the currently executing class was compiled, but the definition can no longer be found.

constructors.name: NoClassDefFoundError
constructors.comment: Constructs a NoClassDefFoundError with no detail message.

constructors.name: NoClassDefFoundError
constructors.comment: Constructs a NoClassDefFoundError with the specified detail message.
